# Free-Tier / Low-Cost AWS Rules

- Optimize for lowest safe cost first; scale complexity only when metrics justify it.
- Use S3 + CloudFront for static content delivery.
- Prefer managed pay-per-use services for low traffic.
- Keep Lambda bundles small and dependencies minimal.
- Reuse SDK clients outside handlers to reduce cold start overhead.
- Set conservative Lambda memory/timeouts, then tune with real metrics.
- Cache aggressively at CloudFront for static and media paths.
- Add cache-control headers intentionally; avoid accidental no-cache defaults.
- Use least-privilege IAM policies for every function/service.
- Create budget alarms and cost anomaly alerts from day one.
- Tag resources by project, environment, and owner for cost visibility.
- Avoid always-on resources unless strictly required.
- Treat cost regressions as production issues and fix quickly.
